    {
      "id": "sybil_16_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_16",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 is a mechanically sound example of the E46 chassis, powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine featuring individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a precise Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-Variable differential lock. The suspension maintains its composure with a stock MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear setup, providing excellent lateral grip and feedback. Recent service includes critical preventative maintenance on the VANOS system and a thorough reinforcement of the rear subframe mounting points. While showing minor cosmetic wear consistent with its age, this M3 remains a performance-focused driver\u2019s car with a robust drivetrain and a linear power band that pulls hard to the 8,000 RPM redline.",
